b0421270-f4c9-45dc-8e2c-5df3003d3c91.3d36d1e4-3d8f-48a3-9ead-6936596b4c6b.description= 
Gets a list of files and folders in a directory.

Input Parameters\:
source - the directory to check
delimiter - A delimiter to put between files and folders in the directory.
username - username to use when reading.
password - password to use when reading.

returns\:
The children of the path.

Extra Results\:
count - the number of children.

Responses\:
failure			- the operation failed. The path probably could not be found, or was a file.
success			- The operation succeeded.
b0421270-f4c9-45dc-8e2c-5df3003d3c91.452fdddd-a311-496b-be84-4ed278736e75.description= 
Checks to see if a path points to a directory.

Input Parameters\:
source - the path to check
username - username to use when reading.
password - password to use when reading.

Responses\:
failure			- the operation failed. The path does not point to a directory.
success			- The operation succeeded.
b0421270-f4c9-45dc-8e2c-5df3003d3c91.4b82b888-cfb3-4170-bf08-051b3841e506.description= 
Compares a files last modified date/time to a given threshold.

Input Parameters\:
source - the file to read
Threshold - the threshold to compare the file modified time to.
username - username to use when reading.
password - password to use when reading.

Responses\:
failure			- the operation failed. The file probably could not be found.
greater than	- The file's modified time is larger than the threshold.
less than		- The file's modified time is smaller than the threshold.
equal to		- The file's modified time is the same as the threshold.

Extra Results\:
date			- The file's modified time.

b0421270-f4c9-45dc-8e2c-5df3003d3c91.b5b972fd-8213-4aac-aaec-c75ed1a65abe.description=Iterates through a list of values.If the list changes while running, the updates will be appended to the list.

Inputs\:
list - The list to iterate through.
separator - A delimiter that separates elements in the list.

Returns\:
The current element of the list, if the response is has more

Responses\:
has more - Another value was in the list, and has been returned.
has no more - The iterator has gone fully through the list. This response will only be returned once per iteration through the list, a subsequent call to the Iterator will restart the Iteration through the list.
failure - failed to process the list.

Note\: Where the iterator is in the list is tracked by each step's unique id. Therefore you can iterate on the same list from multiple steps simultaneously.

WARNING\: Any step that will use the results of this Iterator operation will, by default, attempt to assign that step's inputs from a flow variable. If this is left checked, then the first element of the iterator will be used for every cycle of iteration..

b0421270-f4c9-45dc-8e2c-5df3003d3c91.description=
moves or removes windows log files from a folder.

Inputs\:
alternateStore - Where to put log files. They are deleted if null.
folder - Folder to clean of windows log files.
user - user to authenticate as.
password - password for user.
Old Threshold - Files before this date will be cleaned.

Responses\:
success - operation completed.
failure - something went wrong.
